To fix the problem, you should change the code from `Update()` to `FixedUpdate()` in the script where you are trying to move the Rigidbody. `Update()` is used to update non-physics data, while `FixedUpdate()` should be used for physics calculations. 

The correct version of your code is:

```csharp
public class OVRGrabber : MonoBehaviour
{
    //...

    protected virtual void FixedUpdate()
    {
        if (m_operatingWithoutOVRCameraRig)
        {
            OnUpdatedAnchors();
        }
    }

    void OnUpdatedAnchors()
    {
        //...
    }

    //...
}
```

This version of the code uses `FixedUpdate()` instead of `Update()`, and since physics calculations are performed with `FixedUpdate()`, your Rigidbody should move correctly.

